article.description: Kyle Allman made 8 of 13 from the field, hit 8 of 9 from the free-throw line and finished with 25 points to help Cal State Fullerton beat Long Beach State 81-71 on Saturday night.
article.headline: Allman scores 25 points, CS Fullerton beats Long Beach State
article.linkText: Allman scores 25 points, CS Fullerton beats Long Beach State
article.story: FULLERTON, Calif. -- Kyle Allman made 8 of 13 from the field, hit 8 of 9 from the free-throw line and finished with 25 points to help Cal State Fullerton beat Long Beach State 81-71 on Saturday night. Allman has scored at least 20 points in four consecutive games and seven of his last eight. Khalil Ahmad had 15 points and a career-high seven assists and Jackson Rowe scored 12 points for the Titans (16-10, 9-5 Big West). Ahmad hit a 3-pointer and Arkim Robertson threw down a dunk to cap an 11-0 spurt that spanned halftime and gave Fullerton a 32-29 lead with 18 minutes to play. The Titans used a 10-2 run push their lead into double figures about five minutes later when Allman made back-to-back baskets and Long Beach State (13-17, 7-7) never threatened from there. Levin finished with 18 points and eight rebounds, and Temidayo Yussuf scored 13 for LBSU.
